The paper deals with multiwinner elections, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The use of quantitative techniques and the investigation of election rules suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The study of committee selection and the analysis of different election rules may also fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
